  "prompt": "Why do people always eat doner kebab after getting high?",
  "response": "There is no definitive reason why people may choose to eat doner kebab specifically after getting high, but there are several factors that might contribute to this behavior:\n\n1. **Intense Hunger (the Munchies)**: Consuming cannabis often leads to an increased appetite, commonly referred to as \"the munchies.\" After getting high, people tend to crave food, especially greasy, savory, and filling options. Doner kebab fits this description well.\n\n2. **Accessibility and Availability**: Doner kebab is often available at street food stands, fast food joints, and late-night eateries. This makes it a convenient and quick option for satisfying cravings when people are out and about.\n\n3. **Flavor and Texture**: The combination of juicy meat, flavorful sauces, fresh vegetables, and sometimes crispy bread or fries creates a sensory experience that may be particularly appealing when someone is under the influence of cannabis, which can heighten taste and flavor perceptions.\n\n4. **Cultural Habit**: In many places, especially in cities with diverse food options, doner kebab has become a popular late-night food choice. It\u2019s common for people to associate social activities like partying or relaxing with friends with grabbing a quick, tasty snack, and doner kebab fits well into this scenario.\n\n5. **Comfort Food**: The filling and hearty nature of doner kebab can provide a sense of comfort and satisfaction, which might be particularly desirable when someone is experiencing the effects of cannabis.\n\nUltimately, while these factors provide some context, eating habits after getting high are highly individual and can vary widely from person to person.",
